weekly_top_story.headline: UPS Acquires Andlauer Healthcare Group for $1.6 Billion, Expanding Its Health Care Logistics Footprint
weekly_top_story.summary: UPS finalized the $1.6 billion acquisition of Andlauer Healthcare Group to strengthen its capabilities in temperature-controlled health care logistics, enhancing global shipment visibility and transit times for pharmaceutical and medical device supply chains.

stories.headline: Hippocratic AI Secures $126M Series C Funding to Expand Patient-Facing AI Agents
stories.summary: Hippocratic AI completed over 115 million clinical patient interactions without safety issues and raised $126 million at a $3.5 billion valuation to scale AI-driven patient engagement solutions.

stories.headline: Millions of Americans Brace for Higher Health Insurance Costs as Open Enrollment Begins
stories.summary: The start of open enrollment comes amid rising health insurance premiums and the upcoming expiration of Affordable Care Act subsidies, potentially impacting access and affordability for many patients.

stories.headline: Government Shutdown Raises Concerns Over SNAP Benefits and Healthcare Premiums
stories.summary: With the U.S. government shutdown nearing the longest in history, there is growing uncertainty around SNAP benefits and rising healthcare premiums that could affect vulnerable populations and healthcare coverage.
